 of the job. Featuring new forewords by Chris Holm, Duane Swierczynski, and Laura Lippman—celebrated crime writers, all—these masterworks of noir are the capstone to an extraordinary literary run that will leave you craving more. Written over the course of fifty years, the Parker novels are pure artistry, adrenaline, and logic both brutal and brilliant. Join Parker on his jobs and read them all again or for the first time. But don’t talk to the law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBank robberiesvFiction. 0aCriminalsvFiction. 0aThievesvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  acrime fiction, hard-boiled, hard-bitten, gritty, harsh realism, roman noir, cops, dames, police work, detectives, suspense, mystery, thriller, thrilling, career criminal, fast-paced, engaging, intrigue, ultimate score, heist, elaborate heists, violence, gunplay, fighting, action, adventure, poker game, gambling, messy scam, con artists, armored car, master thief, flawed hero, shady characters, seedy underworld, amoral world, on the run, foul play, revenge.1 aSwierczynski, Duane.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226508511423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226508511/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles